- Install system-wide dependencies libraries:
`sudo apt-get install python-dev libxml2-dev libxslt-dev zlib1g-dev`
`sudo apt-get install libffi-dev`

- Create a virtual environment and use it
`virtualenv .env`
`source ./.env/bin/activate`

- Install script dependencies
`pip install -r ./requirements.txt`

Test installation:
`sudo ./bin/runtest`

You may want to add it to crontab:
`sudo ./bin/add_to_cron.sh`
